inn1.comm: Lovely start from Watto. He leans forward to drive a full delivery that shaped in a bit, straight past the umpire.
outside off stump, full in length, Watson stays back and across and mistimes the cut down to point
this one curves away from Watson who watches it all the way into Dhoni's gloves
length delivery around the off stump line, Watson tries to force it away to the off side off the back foot but edges it towards mid-on for a single
full delivery, lands outside off stump, darts back in but not enough to interest Paine
straighter, lands on a length around middle and off and shapes towards off, Paine makes sure he doesn't get squared-up as he pushes it down the track
Two slips in for Nehra as well. good delivery. It landed on a length and moved back in. Watson is surprised by the inward movement but manages to push it away to the off side.

dead plumb in front. Nehra strikes early. The in ward movement did Watto in. It landed on a length around middle and off and moved back in to evade the defensive poke and strike right in front of the stumps. Gone! The ball is moving around as was expected.
Ponting is welcomed by a bouncer that slants across the batsman.
length delivery moving away from Ricky who lets it go past him. He will bring back one in any time now.
another bouncer, on the middle stump line, Ponting goes for the pull but doesn't connect and it bounds away off the body. He was through the shot rather early there
on the hips, tucked behind square-leg for a single
around the off stump, full in length, slight hint of away movement, squeezed to backward point
loud shout for lbw but umpire Ameish Sahiba negates it. It landed on a length, on the middle and cut in to hit him on the pad. It would have missed leg stump.
Again cutting in but goes down the leg side
oh superb delivery this. Two deliveries that cut in has been followed now by an outswinger. Paine was beaten comprehensively
negates the swing by moving down the track and flicks the full delivery from the middle and leg through midwicket
full delivery outside off stump, stays there and Paine is beaten on the loose drive
edged  but falls well short of the slip cordon. Again, Paine pushed away from his body and got the edge but it dropped short and ran between the first and second slip
lands on a length and moves back in, Ponting lunges across in his typical fashion and the ball runs away off the pad
Crash. It was slightly short and Paine got into the right position to cut it away superbly past point
straighter and Paine gets behind the line to defend to the off side
on that middle stump line, moving in late, Paine does well to ensure his front leg was not pressed across and got his bat in front of the pad to defend
length delivery straightening on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
goes wide of the crease and angles it across Paine who dabs it to point
leans forward to defend rather carefully
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
wild swing and a miss. The swing is causing a few problems here. It was the outswinger and Ricky has a rather unconvincing waft at it
gets forward to squeeze another delivery leaving him to thirdman
teasing outswinger moving away very late and moves past the outside edge of Paine, who was again playing away from the body
around the off stump line, dabbed down to second slip

oh fine delivery this. It landed around the off stump, on a length, and cut back in sharply to trouble Ponting. Ricky didn't expect the ball to move back in that much, tries to stab it but is hit high on the back thigh.
full in length, curving in on the middle, Ponting manages to get an inside edge on that as he looks to defend.
another one that curves back in, Paine has done well against the inswingers so far: he takes care not to push that front leg across unlike Ponting. This one has been dabbed to the on side
Just one slip in now. Length delivery angling across Tim who runs it down to Harbhajan at third man
back of length around the off stump, moving away, Ponting leaned forward, opened the bat-face and punched it on the up through point. Fine shot.
on the pads, rolls away behind the wicket. Ponting must feel he has missed out there. He was looking to glance it but couldn't connect

dropped by Tendulkar at first slip. It was a length delivery that moved away from Paine who pushed at it, bat away from the body, and edged it low to the left of first slip. Tendulkar was late in moving and couldn't quite get down in time. I dare say Rahul Dravid might have caught it !
moves down the leg side
leans forward to defend to the off side
gets forward to dab the ball to short point
cuts in from around the off stump, Paine, who seems better in tackling the incoming delivery than the ones leaving him, pushes it down towards mid-on
outside off stump, back of length ,cut hard but straight to backward point
around the off stump, full in length, pushed to short point
One slip and a short cover in. Ponting stretches out to defend to cover
fuller, on the middle and off, Ponting is hesitantly forward as he defends to the off side
Cracker. It was short in length and outside off, Ponting was up in a flash, carving it beautifully past point. Great to watch. Whaddaplayaaa
leans forward to defend towards mid-off
length delivery around the off stump, steered to backward point. Free hit coming up folks. Here we go.
on the middle stump line, bouncing just over, Ponting has a big slog across the line but misses it completely and Dhoni lunges to his left to take it
on the middle and leg, squirted down to square-leg
on the middle stump line, moving in, worked through midwicket. Jadeja just about manages to pull it back from the ropes. It was sweetly timed shot.
Imperious. It was short in length on the off stump line, Ponting  was on the front foot and he short-arm pulled it high over wide midwicket region. So nonchalantly done, almost dismissive.
Dhoni moves up to the stumps and has to watch as Ponting unfurls some razzmatazz. It was a full length delivery around the off stump and Ponting creams it through extra cover. Easy on the eye.
on the middle and leg, turned down to fine-leg
short in length and width outside off, crashed straight to cover
on the middle stump line, straightening, driven to mid-on
slightly short in length, around the middle and leg, Ponting goes for the drag-pull but misses and is struck on the body
around the off stump line, punched down to mid-off
gets forward to push a length delivery on the middle and off line to covers

top edged over fine-leg boundary! Ponting charged down the track and Nehra fired in a good bouncer. Ponting shut his eyes as he went for the pull and was lucky that the edge took the ball over the fielder placed in the deep
around the off stump, steered to point
Welcome Ishant says Tim. Full delivery on the leg and middle, Tim flicks it over square-leg. Easily done.
full again, just around the middle and off line, sweetly driven back down the track but Ishant swoops down to cut it off.
cuts in from the off stump line, defended to midwicket
short in length, moves in from outside off stump, punched to covers
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
goes back, taps it close on the off side, looks for a single but he slips and falls down! Ponting gets back. Tim has a laugh about it with Raina who had rushed in to pick the ball
leans forward to work the ball from outside off, with the turn, to right of midwicket
that middle and leg line takes the ball down leg. Wide
lands this one outside off but short in length, Tim goes right back to work it past square-leg
leans across to defend a delivery that straightens to the off side
flighted on the middle and off line, full in length, tickled to short fine-leg
drops it slightly short in length, enough for Ricky to get back and cut it hard past point.
turns a bit but again goes down leg, Ponting leaves it all alone
leans forward and across to defend the off break to the on side
drifts down the leg side and there is an appeal for a catch by Dhoni.  It had gone off the pad
full in length, outside off stump, driven to cover
overpitched on the middle and leg, Tim leans forward to whip it between midwicket and mid-on. Nice flick of the wrists and the ball races away
length delivery just outside off stump, defended to the off side

Ishant's best delivery yet. It landed full in length outside off stump and darted back in late. TIm went for the flamboyant off drive, no foot movement, and the ball curved in through the bat and pad gap and rushed past the off stump
walks down the track and deflects the length delivery moving in to midwicket
on the middle stump line, slower through the air this time than the last over, turned to short fine-leg
again slows up the pace, on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
full, really full, on driven down to long-on
goes right back to defend the ball turning in from outside off
aha! the reverse sweep. leans across to play the reverse sweep, and gets it past the diving PKumar at short third man. Harbhajan is not happy with PK's effort. It should have been stopped.
leans forward to push it to the on side for a single
lovely length delivery that straightens outside off, Tim pushes inside the line, expecting the ball to dart back in, and is beaten
drifts to the pads, flicked uppishly to deep square-leg region
cuts in from a length from outside off , defended on the front foot
full delivery outside off, Ponting tried to go for the big extra-cover drive but the ball stopped on him a touch and the bat-handle rotated in his hands and the ball rolled back to Ishant
slower one, dipping full delivery, Ponting checks his shot and deflects the ball to midwicket
Magic from Ricky! It was the full delivery, Ponting eased forward and nonchalantly lifted it straight over the bowler. One bounce and over the ropes. Australia off to a great start
really slow through the air, flighted delivery, Paine is through early with his sweep shot and the ball rolls away to the off side
flighted on the middle and leg, Paine waits for the ball to arrive this time before sweeping it past the short fine-leg fielder
on the middle stump line, defended on the front foot
lands outside off, short in length, spins in, tapped past square-leg for a single
short in length, turns in from outside off, Ponting goes on the back foot and cuts it to sweeper cover
flighted outside off stump, turns in, Tim goes right back to push it to midwicket.

edged but short of Gambhir at third man.  It was the full delivery well outside off stump, Ponting stretched across and went for a big shot and edged it. Gambhir lunged forward but the ball dipped short and hit his body. Gambhir didn't run straight forward initially, seemed to move to his right  before he changed directions
leans well forward to defend
back of length ,cutting in from outside off, defended down the track
in the zone outside off stump, Paine is beaten as the ball straightens.
full in length around the off stump, driven to mid-off
moves in from outside off stump, tries to push it to the on side, rolls away to the off side, over throws as the throw misses the non-striker's end
fine start from Paine. It was slightly short in length outside off, Paine went back to cut it past backward point
goes back to push it to the on side
goes right back to push it past midwicket for a single
on the off stump line, dabbed to point region for a easy single
just outside off, Paine goes back and across to turn it to right of midwicket
leans across to defend to the off side
walks down the track and punches on the up, down to sweeper cover
on the middle stump line, full in length, deflected to right of mid-on and that's 100 up.
full in length, straightening outside off stump, squeezed to point
moves to his 3rd ODI fifty with a push towards mid-on for a quick single. Good start from Paine. Can he go on and make a hundred here
full and on the middle stump line, on driven to deepish mid-on for a single
Short and wide, bouncing away, Paine went for the cut but got the top-edge through to Dhoni. The shot was there to be played but perhaps done in by the extra bounce.
on the off stump line, driven towards sweeper cover
on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
pushes it towards backward point, Ponting wants the single, White wasn't sure but they get across as PK makes a complete mess of a regulation stop
leans forward to defend to the off side
gets on the back foot to push it towards long-of where the sub fielder Amit Mishra fumbles! And he almost twists his ankle in the process
short in length around off stump, pushed down to long-on
fullish, on the middle, on driven to long-on for a single
full delivery outside off, straightens and White stumbles forward and is comprehensively beaten. Slip in place as well. Good delivery that.
short in length, well outside off, left alone easily
on the off stump line, pushed to mid-on; Ponting wants a run but White screams out a big NO NO NO
short in length outside off stump, White mistimes the intended punchy shot back to Ishant
full in length, straightening again, driven to mid-off
"caught" at sweeper cover by Harbhajan. It was banged in short and White carved it up and over the off-side field
leans forward to defend to the off side
flighted outside off, slower through the air, defended to point
slightly short, forced away to deep cover for a single
slightly short, cut down to backward point where Tendulkar fumbles to give away a run
nicely done. It was slightly outside off, Ponting moves back and across to cut it past backward point. Fifty up and he is all smiles as he raises his bat in the air
lands outside off, spins away, left alone
full in length, straightening outside off, driven sweetly but straight to mid-off
on the middle stump line, shaping in, White had pressed his front leg across, gets his bat around the front pad to push the ball to right of mid-on
lands back of length, cuts back in, Ponting stretches well forward to defend compactly
slightly slower, driven back to Ishant who threatens to throw it at the striker's end.
length delivery outside off, superbly driven on the up and Harbhajan does well at deep cover to move to his right and make a sliding stop.
cuts in from just outside off, Ponting crouches to squeeze it to square-leg
leans forward to defend
gets forward to place it to left of cover fielder
takes it from outside off and paddle sweeps it to fine-leg. Very well done. Ishant manages to stop it near the ropes.
leans forward to defend to the off side

not so easy chance missed flighted up outside off, Ponting lofted it high towards long-off, Nehra was inside the line and jumped up with his left hand stretched out but ended up palming  it over him! He was inside the ropes, had he stayed near the ropes, he would have caught it
leans forward to push it to the off side for a single
gets forward to push it to the on side
low dipping full toss, gently pushed down to long-on
goes back to steer it to point for a single
gets on the front foot to defend the off break that landed outside off
flighted full around off stump, driven down to long-on
on the off stump line, turned past square-leg for a single
leans well forward to defend to the off side
slightly short, cut straight to Raina at cover
on the length, around off stump, Ponting gets well forward to defend
charges down the track but is beaten in the flight and ends up slicing it in the air through the off side and it rolls down to sweeper cover
flighted around off stump line, defended to cover
on the middle and leg, turns down leg, Ponting went back to glance it past the diving Sehwag at short fine-leg region
well outside off this time, pinches a single with a gentle push to point
turns in to the middle, deflected to midwicket
the topspinner around the off stump line, White shapes to play to the on side and gets a leading edge to backward point
leans forward to drive it to long-off
turns it towards midwicket and rushes fora quick single... Raina moved to his right and fired in a direct hit at the striker's end but White is home. It was referred upstairs.
slightly short, Ponting cuts straight to backward point. He has missed out on a boundary there
fuller and Ponting comes forward to defend
rocks back to ping sweeper cover
goes for the big slog sweep but misses it completely. The ball landed outside off and spun away
shout for lbw. It was the arm-ball but it would have missed the leg stump. White was beaten by the inward movement
goes right back to defend cautiously
leans well forward to turn it to right of midwicket
leans forward to squeeze the off break to square-leg
on the off and middle line, swept around to short fine-leg
on the middle stump line, worked away to deep midwicket
leans well forward to push it back to Harbhajan
slightly short, cut down hard to deep cover
leans forward and chips it in the air towards long-on for a single
gets on the back foot and cuts it down to backward point

Plumb in front. Ponting doesn't look happy. It landed on a length on the middle and leg, turned in past the defensive push and hit him on the back pad right in front of middle stump. Dead plumb. Fine innings comes to an end.
spins in from outside off, goes right back to defend
on the back foot, squeezed to backward point
stays back to work it past square-leg
flighted from round the stumps, on driven to Ishant at long-on
flighted from over the stumps to the right-hander, again pushed down to long-on
well outside off stump, punched down to sweeper cover
on the middle stump line, turned to left of short fine-leg
flighted outside off stump, pushed out to cover
quicker, but short in length, punched away to deep midwicket
flighted outside off, on driven to long-on
on the middle, driven to left of Jadeja who makes a fine diving stop
on the middle and off, pushed to right of extra cover where Raina makes lovely diving stop.
stays back to stab it away to the off side
on the off stump line, pushed out to Raina at short extra cover
on the middle and leg, squeezed down to fine-leg region
doosra makes its appearance. on the middle and leg, White tries to flick and gets a leading edge back down the track
on the off stump line, defended to the off side
gets forward and picks up a single with a push-drive to long-on
short and wide, cut easily well to the right of sweeper cover. That was a hit-me ball.
leans well forward to defend
retains the strike with an off drive
gets forward to on drive to long-on
on the middle stump line, defended on the front foot
picks it from the off stump and paddles it to fine-leg region
tapped towards short thirdman fora single
taps it close on the off side and rushes across
Dhoni is standing up to the stumps. Full and straight, defended carefully down the track
moves outside leg, follows him, pushed back to the bowler
worked away to the on side
rotates the strike with a dab shot
whack. It was banged in too short and White pulls it away to wide midwicket boundary. That sat up and begged to be hit; White obliged
moves outside leg, slips in a slower one, stabbed to point
slower one on the legs, nudged away
slips down leg side and all Hussey needed to do was to get bat on ball and he does so with a little glance shot
around the off stump this time, tapped towards point for a quick single
on the middle stump line, full, pushed back to Nehra
leans forward to push it to cover point for a single
slower one, the off cutter, white adjusts late and stabs it to the off side
moves forward to on drive it for a single
White breaks free with a charge down the track. He reaches the pitch of the ball and swings it high over wide long-on. Maximum!
pushed through quicker, defended down the track
almost drops it in the blockhole, dug out to the off side
really full again, pushed down to long-on
another slower one, bunted out to covers
Violence. banged in short and White opens his stance and pulls it to wide midwicket boundary. That was hit hard.
fuller, just outside off stump, whipped down to long-on
fullish, moving in from just outside off, Hussey holds his balance and creams it inside-out to right of mid-off. Very well played. Sweetly timed.
slower one, outside off, dabbed down to third man
moves in from outside off stump, defended to covers
allows it to come in before wristing it through midwicket
slower one, very full outside off, White reaches out to squeeze it to backward point
from round the stumps, moves in to the middle and off line, pushed out to cover point
slower one, on the middle, White stumbles out to defend
another slower one, the off cutter, White checks his shot and in the end stabs it away
leans forward to paddle it away
turns from the stumps, Hussey stays back to open the bat face and guides it to third man ... Ishant tries to make a diving stop but can't
leans well forward to push it to covers
goes right back to work it to midwicket
on the middle stump line, turned to midwicket
slower through the air, goes for the sweep but misses it completely
fullish on the middle stump line, driven down to long-on
on the middle stump line, pushed out to the on side
length delivery around the off stump, mistimes the drive to long-off
low dipping full toss around the off stump and White stretches out to crash it to cover boundary
whips the full delivery from outside off to long-on
charges down the track and pushes it to long-off
full delivery outside off stump, White reaches his fifty with a cover drive
full in length, from round the stumps, driven down to long-off
full delivery well outside off, Whtie lets it go thinking it might be called wide but it isn't that wide
fullish delivery well outside off, goes for the big drive, edges it to on side
moves down the track and drives to long-off
full in length, on the middle stump line, deflected to the on side

White falls after taking the batting powerplay. It was the full delivery outside off, White tried to fetch it from there with a big slog but ended up slicing it high to extra cover where Raina waits patiently for the ball to dip into his palms
full in length around the off stump line, pushed out to right of mid-off
full and slanting away, pushed out to short extra cover
slower one, around off stump, stabbed to right of short extra cover where Raina charges out but can't prevent the quick single
fullish, outside off stump line, dabbed to left of third man where PK cleans up
turns in from the off stump line, tries to turn it to the on side, misses and is hit on the pad
doosra on the off stump line, dabbed to point
turns in, whipped to deep square-leg region
tossed up on the off stump line, spins in, Vogues goes for the slog sweep but gets more elevation than distance and is caught in the deep
short in length on the middle and off line, turned to midwicket
just outside off stump, punched to covers
around the off stump line, worked past square-leg and he rushes back for the second run. Gambhir with the throw but Hussey dives back in
banged in short, goes for the pull but doesn't connect properly
gets forward to push it to long-on
on the middle and leg line, turned past square-leg
full delivery on the off stump line, just short of the blockhole, dug out just past the bowler
Hopesy! he leans well forward to crash a slower one high over long-off. Superbly struck.
on a length, around middle and off, another slower one, turned to the on side
banged in short outside off, Hopes waits for it to arrive before carving it high over backward point
low full toss, going for the yorker, works it to deep midwicket
yorker length, squeezed out to the bowler
drags it short and Hussey wallops it high over to midwicket boundary. What a fine innings this has been. He has stealthily moved up to 49
leans forward to flick it to deep backward square-leg. That's his 25th ODI fifty
Hopes is run out . pulls it to midwicket. Hopes has charged down the track too much but Hussey changed his mind after taking couple of steps. Sehwag throws it to Nehra who calmly breaks the stumps.
drag pulls it away to the on side
on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
Thrash. What a smoking shot. It was full and outside off, Hussey crashed it through extra cover.
another one but no violence this time. It was the slower one outside off, Hussey waited on the front foot before timing it superbly well to the left of sweeper cover
yorker length from round the stumps, dug out through covers
moves outside leg and slices the full toss to deep point
aha! cheeky. He crouched forward, picked the full toss from the off stump and paddled it past the short fine-leg fielder. Neat.
yet another full toss, smashed hard past the bowler
slower one this time, Johnny boy waits and waist before smashing it to wide midwicket boundary.
banged in short, shapes to pull but doesn't connect properly

Massive! Whoa what a big hit that was. Husseeeeeeeeeyyy! He charged down the track, picked the slower one and hammered it way over the straight boundary. The new ball has come out! Hussey is all smiles.
low full toss, on the off stump line, mistimes the drive to long-on
the runs are coming in a flood here. Mitch drag-heaves this delivery to deep backward square-leg boundary. Aussies are charging away in some style
Hussey falls after a wonderful knock. Hilditch must be watching closely. He dragged the ball from outside off and heaved it to deep midwicket
from round the stumps, full delivery, goes past the attempted big heave and goes through to Dhoni
low full toss on the middle stump line, flat-batted to long-off
banged in short, straight, Lee goes for the upper cut but doesn't connect
another swing and a miss. short and wide, it was there to be hit but Lee couldn't get wood on leather
full delivery, lee tries to squeeze it out to the on side, misses it and it deflects off the back pad on to the stumps

inn2.comm: What a start. Just like Watto in the first innings, Sehwag starts off with a boundary. Full and outside off, swinging away, Sehwag reaches out to lash it over point.
Another one. Fullish, on the middle and leg, whipped through midwicket.
cuts in from the off stump line, rolls off the pad to the off side and Tendulkar calls him over for a single
leans well forward to defend to the off side
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
thinks about driving but sees the away swing and lets the ball go through
pushes it wide down the leg side and Tim Paine can't quite get behind it and the ball bursts through the gloves
Crash. Short and outside off stump, Sehwag stays adjacent to the line to blast it up and over point. The crowd roar
moves in towards middle and leg, turned past square-leg
cuts in towards middle, nudged to the on side
comes forward to push the ball from off and middle to the on side for a single
cuts in and that cramps up Sehwag who steers it to point
again moves in, Sehwag comes forward to push it out to covers
full delivery, hint of away swing and that gets Sachin to get a leading edge on the drive
in the channel outside off, Tendulkar watches it all the way into Paine's gloves
moves in towards middle and leg, turned softly to square-leg
short and outside off, Tendulkar cuts hard but straight down to third man
homing in on the off stump, Sehwag is back and plays a compact defensive stroke
on the off stump line, short in length, that length allows him to work it to midwicket
short in length ,cutting in to middle and off, Tendulkar tries to punch it on the up but edges it to square-leg
leans forward to square drive to covers
gets forward to drive to the on side
SRT breaks free with a whip to square-leg boundary. It drifted a bit towards middle and leg, enough for Tendulkar to work his wrists overtime
swing and a miss. Full and outside off, Tendulkar tried to carve it to point but doesn't connect
gets cautiously behind the line of this length delivery on the off stump line and defends
lovely yorker on the off stump line, dug out
full delivery, hint of away swing,  Sehwag tries to flick it across the line from just around off stump but the ball moves away slightly to catch the outside edge. Gone!
lands on a length outside off and moves away, left alone
really full delivery around off, pushed out to point
slower one outside off, jabbed out to short cover
length delivery around the off stump line, Gambhir eases forward, opens the bat-face and square drives it to point boundary
length delivery moving away from the off stump, Tendulkar tries to punch on the up but the bat came down in an angle and he is beaten
Mitchell Johnson has twisted his ankle It was pushed to extra cover where he bent down to stop but seems to have twisted his ankle. The physio was out. He looks okay now
full in length, angling away from Gambhir who runs it down to third man
Tendulkar is again beaten on the square drive. Again, the bat came down n an angle. He is yet to find his groove here
and he is beaten again. This time on the cover drive.
lets this one go through to Paine
on the legs, Gambhir flicks it away for a single
low full toss outside off, Tendulkar slices it straight to backward point.
moves in towards off and middle, fullish, pushed back to the bowler
goes for that square drive again but can't beat cover point. Four men in the off-side ring.
short in length, punched sweetly this time but Vogues dives to his right at backward point to make a superb half-stop
leans forward to defend a length delivery
back of length around off, Tendulkar stands up on his toes to punch it to short cover
fuller and wider this time and Tendulkar moves forward to crash it to left of mid-off
picks a single this time with a push to left of mid-off
full in length, eased past the non-striker, mid-off rushes to his right and puts in a desperate dive but the ball rushes past him
lands outside off stump and moves further away, left alone
fullish, outside off, opens the bat-face and drives it to Lee at wide third man

Ricky Ponting takes a neat  catch at short extra cover. Tendulkar drove on the up to left of Ponting who flung himself to take a sharp catch. Two down and wobbling. Australia move into the driver's seat.
fullish, outside off, squeezed past backward point
on the pads, tries to clip it away,  misses and is struck on the pad
on the middle stump line, turned to midwicket
length delivery outside off stump line, left alone
on the middle, straightening a touch, worked to square-leg.
leans across to steer to backward point
on the middle and leg, clipped down to fine-leg
short in length, bouncing outside off, taps it close on the off side, wants a single but Virat sends him back
short in length, edged behind the wicket and they rush across for a quick single
bouncing into rib-cage, fended away to fine-leg region
lands on a good length on the off, defended solidly towards cover
too straight, on middle and leg, tickled away behind square for a single
bowled full on the off, presents the full face and drives it back to the bowler
short of a good length on the off, drops it just wide of the stumps, thinks of a single but it's not available
banged in short on middle, tried to work it away into the leg side, was struck on the arm, no single on offer
back of a length on the off, drops it into the off side and thinks of a single but he can't get it
back of a length on the off, guided down to third man for a single
banged in short outside off, leaps and runs it down to third man for one more
testing him on a length outside off, gets forward and taps it down towards extra cover
bowled it in the blockhole on the off, dug out towards cover
angling it on the pads, turned away towards fine leg for a single
nicely timed, fullish, in the slot outside off, he gets to the pitch and punches it past the bowler to beat mid-off to the ropes
hurled it full on the off, driven down towards cover from the crease
pitched up and punished, tempting length outside off, his eyes lit up, charged forward and drilled it down the ground past mid-off
knocks it down in front of cover and point for a single
shortish on middle, closes the face and turns it down towards fine leg for a single
hurled it short on leg stump, tries to whip it fine, struck on the hips, manages a run
short of a good length on the off, defended watchfully back to the bowler
full and down the leg side, bowled at 141 kmph, tries to glance it fine, misses, the keeper fumbles to allow them a single
in the channel outside off, opens the face to guide it down to point
bowled full on the off, driven crisply but straight to extra cover
knocked down towards point, Gambhir calls for a single and is sent back, the fielder hurls a throw at the non-striker's end and it catches Gambhir on the back
banged in short outside off, played it well, taking his bottom-hand off and played it wide of the keeper
short and wide and he took full toll, slashing it hard over point for a boundary
slightly short outside off, guided down towards third man to keep the strike
tight line just a fraction outside off, defended towards cover
fullish on the off, defended with bat close to pad on the off side
rolling his fingers over it, slower one, taps it to third man for a single
nagging line and length, short of a good length on the off, cuts away a hint, defended awkwardly back to the bowler
short and wide, gets a single down to third man to keep the strike
short in length, moving away, guided down to third man
leans well forward to drive to short cover
short in length, cutting in, defended to the on side
on a length, on the off stump line, guided to point
from round the stumps, full and moving in, pushed gently towards mid-on
short in length and outside off, Virat cuts it hard but Vogues makes a fine diving stop at backward point
on a length around off stump, defended to covers
slightly short, pulled down to fine-leg region
full and on the middle and leg, turned to deep square-leg

loud shout for lbw. It landed on a length on the off and cut in sharply and struck Kohli in front of the leg. The umpire reckoned it would have missed leg ; Hawk Eye says it would have hit the leg stump
Flamboyant hit over long-on. He just leaned forward and knifed through the line
from round the stumps wide outside off
fullish, on the off stump line, whipped down to mid-on
short and wide, cut down to left of sweeper cover
yorker on the middle stump, Gambhir stops his front foot movement, gets the bat in front to dig it out to the off side
outside off stump, from that round-arm action which meant the ball shaped away a touch, guided down to third man
from round the stumps to the right-hander, short delivery and Kohli unfurls a wristy pull over midwicket
slanting in from that angle, turned to the on side for a easy single
on the off and middle, from round the stumps, driven to long-off
from over the stumps, turns in from outside off, dabbed toward short midwicket for a single
flighted full, driven back to the bowler
slows up the pace, flighted full, driven down to long-off
slightly short, cut down to sweeper cover
flighted just outside off, Kohli tries to work it to the on side and is struck on the pad just outside off stump
flighted outside off stump, Kohli tries to work it to the on side and is struck just outside off stump
spins away from Gambhir who is beaten, trying to dab it away
leans forward to stab it to the on side
gets forward to defend
goes right back to defend to the off side
really full delivery, Gambhir was trying to back away, intending to push it to point for a single, but realises the length late but manages to adjust and stabs it away
worked away for an easy single
outside off stump, spins in, pushed back to the bowler
moves down the track and drives to long-off

Virat is once again caught at long-off. We have seen that quite often in the IPL and Champions League games as well. He charged down the track but was beaten in flight, tried to go though with the shot and skied it up. Watson ran in from long-off to take a good catch
stretches forward to defend to the on side
moves down the track and drives to long-on
flighted from round the stumps to the lefty Gambhir who drives to long-off
lunges out to push it to the off side
stretches forward and is hit on the pad well outside off
flicked from outside off past square-leg
On the leg stump line, flicked past square-leg
stretches across to defend to Ponting at that close-in position
drops it short and Gambhir jumps at the opportunity; he pulls it away to square-leg boundary
gets forward to ping long-on
full on the off stump, edges the off drive towards non-striker and the bowler lunges to his right to stop
slightly short in length, tries to cut but edges it to the off
on the leg stump line, tries to sweep it really fine, misses and collects a leg bye
from round the stumps, yorker length on the middle, dug out to the off side
length delivery on the off, pushed out to short cover
fuller, dragged behind square-leg for a single
on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
lands on a length, moves in, clipped to the on side
pushed out towards mid-off, there is confusion about the single, Gambhir sends back and he makes it easily as the fielder doesn't pick up the ball cleanly
tries to punch on the up but doesn't quite time the ball well and the bowler stops it

almost run out He moved outside leg, the bowler followed him with a short delivery to cramp him, flat-batted towards mid-off but Ponting rushes from short extra cover to intercept it with a dive. He then fires in a direct hit at the striker's end and the ball ricochets off the sticks. It was referred upstairs
on the pads, tucked behind square-leg
full in length, straightens outside off, left alone
lovely yorker on the off and middle, Dhoni digs it out back to the bowler
short delivery, goes for the pull and drags it to deep backward square-leg
bangs in a bouncer, Dhoni goes for the pull but pulls out at the end as the ball climbs higher than he anticipated
length delivery on the off and middle, pushed to right of short extra cover
length delivery holding its line on the off stump, defended to short extra cover
length delivery around the off stump line, pushed out to deep cover
from round the stumps, slower one, Gambhir backs away to cut it down to deep cover region where Marsh fumbles to give away an extra run
moves outside leg again, Lee follows him with a fast ball, dabbed to right of backward point for a single
full delivery slanting down leg, Gambhir goes for a big swing over midwicket, misses and is struck on the pad and he goes down on to the ground as he loses balance
length delivery just outside off, run down to third man
Dhoni goes downtown. he picked the full delivery from outside off and swung it high over mid-on
low dipping delivery outside off, stabbed close on the off side and they rush across
short in length, cut away but can't beat backward point

nicely done. It was a back-of-length delivery just outside off, Gambhir waited before he opened the bat-face at the last minute and late cut it through vacant slip region and third man couldn't stop it
slower one outside off, Dhoni uses his bottom-hand to power his drive to left of mid-off where Mitch makes a half-stop
on the middle and leg, from round the stumps, tucked to the on side for a quick single
on the middle, skidding towards middle and leg, dabbed to midwicket for a single
drifting to the pads and Gambhir goes back to clip it to backward square-leg boundary .. very well timed..
just outside off stump this time, run down to third man for a run
leans forward to push it to cover

caught right in front by the low dipping full toss. It was dipping in front of leg and middle stump and Gambhir stumbled a bit while trying to get forward and flick it. He missed and was struck dead plumb.
And no surprise, the first ball to Raina is a bouncer. Raina jumps to push it down the track. Here we go. This should get interesting.
fullish, flicked away for a single
crash. Back of length outside off, Dhoni goes back and across to cut it hard to point boundary
from round the stumps, full in length, driven on the up to deep cover
short delivery that doesn't climb all that much, Raina hops and pushes inside the line as the ball flies through to Paine
length delivery outside off, Dhoni stays back to force it down to sweeper cover
full in length on the leg and middle line, wristed to deep midwicket
big swing and a miss. It was angling away from Raina who tried to heave it over mid-on but couldn't connect. Pressure. The crowd sigh.
on the leg and middle, moving towards middle, defended to the on side. Watson stands and stares down the track, Gambhir walks towards square-leg.
back of length delivery outside off, Raina goes for the cut but is beaten by the lack of bounce and it bounces once before it went to Paine

Shot! Stunning. It was short in length, Raina opened his stance, shifted his weight to the back foot and pulled it high over wide midwicket boundary. They are dancing in the aisles, as Tony Greig might have pointed out.
short in length, powered away to deep cover
length delivery on the middle, turned towards midwicket, Dhoni wants a single, Raina doesn't and Dhoni rushes back

Done in by the slower one. Raina was completely fooled; he lunged out and checked his drive and the ball popped back to the delighted Mitch. And this chase continues to be topsy turvy. Silence in the crowd.
low full toss well down the leg side and Paine makes a tumbling half-stop
short in length ,cut down to backward point for a single
full in the zone outside off stump, Jadeja is beaten on the drive
back of length, bouncing on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
short in length around off stump, punched to covers but wont be able to get a run

And Australia on the ascendancy here. Dhoni charged out for the big shot but mistimed it straight to mid-on. Lee throws the ball up in the air and Dhoni crashes his bat onto the ground. Joy and sorrow collide.
short in length and oh boy it's a boundary! I was about to type short in length and pushed past point. It was a mere punch-steer but the timing is good and the ball has raced away to the boundary
drifting to the middle and leg, flicked away to deep for a single
slower one, outside off, cut down to backward point. Jadeja wanders towards square-leg.
Watto! It was crashed down the track but Watson gets down in time to make a half-stop
on the pads, turned past square-leg for couple of runs
low dipping full toss, flicked in the air but drops short of midwicket fielder
slips down the leg side and it will be a wide
short in length, goes for the cut but the bounce gets big on him and he edges it behind the wicket. Jadeja runs blindly for a single but Harbhajan quickly send him back
climbing delivery outside off, jabbed away. Another dot ball. Pressure builds up.
ah.. Mitch drifts another one wide down the leg side. He now runs back to the top of his run-up
short in length, on the middle, Jadeja stands on his toes to clip it behind square-leg
from round the stumps now, slants it into the rib cage, clipped away neatly for couple of runs
leans across and forward and is struck on the pad, And it hits him in line with the stumps and would have hit the off and middle. Hauritz did appeal but turned down
turns this one behind square-leg
aha! Harbhajan goes for the reverse sweep, misses and the ball bounds away off his body
lovely delivery ... lures Jadeja forward before spinning away past the outside edge

he survived a close shout couple of balls earlier but not now. It landed on a length on the middle and off line, Jadeja went for the sweep, missed and was struck in front. It would have hit the off stump. And then they were three.
flighted full outside off, hit on the pad but outside the off stump line
full and outside off, dragged across to midwicket
from round the stumps, Habrhajan walks down the track and drags his pull to fine-leg
stays back to defend a length delivery back to the bowler
lunges out to push the full delivery to covers
fires a bouncer from over the wicket this time. PK is cramped up and is hit on the glove as he tries to fend it away
on the middle and leg, lapped around the corner but straight to Watson at short fine-leg
flighted ever so slowly around off, PK is early into the drive and lobs it past the non-striker
turns in from outside off, late cut to short third-man region
goes back to work it past square-leg
he goes for another reverse sweep and again doesn't connect properly
leans forward to drive it back to the bowler
slower one outside off stump, dabbed away for a single
another slower one, Harbhajan is early in to the swing across the line and collects a leg bye
PK goes over long-off. He read the slower one early, waited and swung it high over the boundary. He then walks across to have a chat with his partner
rotates the strike with a push to long-off
Bhaji and Mitch! It was crashed hard to right of long-on where Mitchell parries it back inside the arena as he treads carefully to avoid stepping on the boundary line
outside off stump and Paine collects
on the middle, swatted to midwicket for a single
turns in sharply, PK was looking for the cut but bails out with a stab to short third man
Dropped by Shaun Marsh, the sub. Praveen picked the flighted delivery from outside off and slog swept it high to deep midwicket where Marsh makes a complete mess. What a clanger
tries to cut and is beaten by the turn and bounce
moves down the track and smothers the turn ,,,
allows for the ball to turn before dabbing it late but straight to short third man
full and well outside off stump, Praveen lets it go
short in length, on the middle, turned to midwicket
picks the slower one early, it was short as well, and Harbhajan slaps it to wide midwicket boundary
well outside off, reaches out to push it out towards long-off
full and well outside off, PK throws the kitchen sink at it but slices it away to third man
again well outside off, almost a wide, Harbhajan reaches out to poke it away to covers
Massive! He took couple of steps down the track and heaves the delivery from well outside off to wide long-on boundary. The crowd find their voice again and the ball is lost. New balls please.
slows up the pace, dabbed towards short third man for a single
flighted delivery outside off, PK has a big swing at it and gets a lucky edge to third man boundary. The crowd think its still possible. They again cheer loudly.
flatter, quicker, defended to the off side
slightly short in length ,cut down to sweeper cover
moves down the track, Hauritz floats it further outside off, Harbhajan reaches out and drags it to deep midwicket
full and outside off, hammered away but straight to sweeper cover. Harbhajan gets across to have a chat with PK.
jumps down the leg side and Watson cleverly fires it well outside off  and PK can't reach it
again full outside off, PK goes for the big drive and slices it to third man
shuffles across to the off side, WAtto pushes it further outside off, hit down to long-off
PK probably knew this one too would be well outside off, so leaned over quickly, opened the bat-face and sliced the full toss to backward point boundary
another full toss, hit hard but straight down to long-off
well down the leg side and Paine does well to collect it
still from round the stumps, on the middle stump line, squeezed to backward point
What a stunner! It was the waist-high full toss, from round the stumps, and Harbhajan just swatted it away over fine-leg boundary

Even better. It was full delivery - Siddle still operating from round the stumps - Habrhajan walks across, steadies himself, clears the front foot and some how manages to wrist it to deep backward square-leg boundary. Neatly done.
now he moves to over the stumps. Really full delivery outside off, Harbhajan tries to squeeze it to third man but no wood on leather. Dot ball.
yorker length delivery, goes past the attempted jab and between Harbhajan's legs
another yorker, dug out towards co ver, Ponting rushes forward and puts in a desperate dive but cant' reach it
full delivery outside off, sliced away to covers where White makes a tumbling stop
Full toss well outside the off stump, PK reaches out to drive and edges it through vacant slip region. Crowd are going mad here
What is happening out there. WAtson shrugs his shoulder in apology. It was another full toss and PK slams it to extra cover boundary.
full delivery but not a full toss, carved away to deep point region

WAtson keeps bowling well outside off again and again and the batsman have by now well caught on to that fact. Harbhajan moves towards off and slices it over backward point. Marsh rushes across and tries a tumbling stop but the ball goes through his grasp

Harbhajan has got the crowd going. Kohli jumps up and down in the dressing room. It was yet another full toss, would you believe it. Pressure. Tension. Harbhajan waited on the back foot and slapped it high over backward point. Super slice. Gone up and over!
goes for the yorker, lands up short of the block hole and its on the legs as well but PK can' connect; the ball rolls of the pad to short fine-leg

Clatter! The off stump has been pegged back. Siddle roars and the crowd applaud the departing Harbhajan. He opened up his stance and tried to swing the length delivery across the line but missed. Timber! Enter Ashish Nehra. what a fine knock this has been from Harbhajan.
goes for the yorker, just about squeezed out to the on side and PK rushes across. It's up to him now. Siddle V PK.
really full delivery on the middle, dug out back down the track, Siddle jumps to stop it . the ball bounds behind him... The batsmen think about a single but decide against it as Siddle rushes back
just a single. Another really full delivery, dug out towards midwicket. The batsmen get across for a chat. Gary kirsten stares ahead from his position.
And Australia win the thriller. Full delivery, driven down to Lee, who has only bowled six overs, at long-on. Phew. What a game. Immense fun.
